entries.repair_kit_ship_d: This repair kit can be used to repair all ship components and chassis. It cannot be used to patch plasma conduits.
entries.plasma_conduit_interior_d: This is a high energy plasma conduit. They are very fragile and prone to bursting. If they burst, IMMEDIATELY evacuate the area as the high energy plasma is very dangerous. Any components attached to this conduit will suffer sustained damage as long as the conduit is broken. These conduits must be patched using conduit patch kits. These can be purchased from your local Shipwright.
entries.yacht_deed_failed: You cannot unpack the deed at this time.
entries.generic_shield_d: This is a shield generator. Shield generators generate a protective shell of energy around your ship. A single generator will protect both the front and rear of your ship. If your shield is damaged, the geneator will recharge the damage over time. If the generator itself is damaged, it will not regenerate. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_reactor_d: This is a reactor. This component powers all of your other ship components. If your reactor fails any component that consumes power will shut down. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_droid_interface_d: This is a droid interface. This will allow you to equip a flight computer or astromech droid on your starship. These can be used to control your ships subsystems. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_capacitor_d: This is a weapon capacitor. Every shot that a weapon fires will drain energy from the capacitor. When this is empty, your weapons will no longer be able to fire until it recharges. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_booster_d: This is a booster. It will allow your ship to temporarily accelerate and improve your top speed. By default, the 'B' key controls your booster. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_engine_d: This is an Engine. This component controls your ships flight performance, speed and handling. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.generic_weapon_d: This is a ship weapon. It is is used to destroy enemy ships. The weapon is powered by both a capacitor and your ship's reactor. Every shot will drain energy from your capacitor. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.

entries.weapon_subpro_tripleblaster_d: gets its name from a three-tiered particle acceleration process. The SubPro line is known for their high kinetic damage potential and low energy consumption. Critics of the SubPro manufacturer complain that high usage results in more wear-and-tear than their competitors, however.
entries.weapon_slayn_ioncannon_d: The standard in non-lethal starship weaponry - Slayn & Korpil employs the most reliable ionic particle stream technology on the market.
entries.weapon_incom_disruptor_d: Long-range starship disruptor technology has been a staple of the INCOM corporation development repertoire for only a few cycles. Although the newest weapons in this line are rather stable, the older post-experimentation models are notoriously twitchy and unreliable.

entries.navicomputer_6_d: Flight Computers are used to store ship management system parameter profiles that can alter ship power allocation during flight. Some starships use astromechs to perform this function instead of flight computers. Once a flight computer has been initialized, programmed data chips can be transferred to its datapad. When a flight computer is associated with a starship, any programs in its datapad will be useable by the pilot once the ship is in space.

entries.generic_armor_d: This is a piece of starship armor plating. This is your second layer of defense behind your shields. To equip ship components, go to a starship terminal and click
. This will allow you to equip this item as well as compare attributes with your current components.
entries.engine_qualdex_kyromaster_d: Massive starship power and maneuverability at an affordable price. The Qualdex
line is a superb addition to any high-performance starship. Perfect for quick interdictions and the long-haul through deep space.
entries.engine_novaldex_eventhorizon_d: Novaldex pushes the starship performance envelope with the J-77
engine. Much more power per cubic centimeter than its predecessor (the J-65), and considerable energy economy when compared to other high-performance sublight engines.
